formatted: On the night the Lakers unveiled their banner for winning the In-Season Tournament, they were never able get into a collective rhythm offensively and could not come up with the key defensive stops they needed in a 114-109 loss to the Knicks on Monday night. The loss is the Lakers third in four games since winning the IST title vs. the Pacers and drops them to 15-12 on the season.

documents.name: Yelling
documents.label: Yelling
formatted: “When we met, she met me partying and hanging out with friends. Now she gets mad at me for doing the things that she met me doing.”

content.text: Yelling
“When we met, she met me partying and hanging out with friends. Now she gets mad at me for doing the things that she met me doing.”

“I know,” I say. “It feels like it’s always one sided. Like with my ex-girlfriend, I was always doing the wrong thing. She always said I was too busy hanging out with my friends and not paying enough attention to her. Everyone became friends with her, but she would say...”
“They are YOUR friends.”

“Right. You know, I loved her. And sometimes it's hard for me to love someone. But when I do, I try my hardest. It’s like I yell and yell, and then I lose my voice, and the things I was screaming to say, goes quiet, and is replaced in the silence.”
